    <item>
      <title>Convergence of the perimeter of an inscribed regular polygon</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/convergence-of-the-perimeter-of-an-inscribed-regular-polygon/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 18 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/convergence-of-the-perimeter-of-an-inscribed-regular-polygon/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Consider a &lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;katex-mathml&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;n&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;n&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;katex-html&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;base&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;strut&#34; style=&#34;height:0.4306em;&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mord mathnormal&#34;&gt;n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;-sided regular polygon inscribed in a circle of radius&#xA;&lt;span class=&#34;katex&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;katex-mathml&#34;&gt;&lt;math xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&#34;&gt;&lt;semantics&gt;&lt;mrow&gt;&lt;mi&gt;r&lt;/mi&gt;&lt;/mrow&gt;&lt;annotation encoding=&#34;application/x-tex&#34;&gt;r&lt;/annotation&gt;&lt;/semantics&gt;&lt;/math&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;katex-html&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;base&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;strut&#34; style=&#34;height:0.4306em;&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mord mathnormal&#34; style=&#34;margin-right:0.02778em;&#34;&gt;r&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. The summits of the polygon lie on the circle, and all sides&#xA;of the polygon are of equal length. The angle at the center of a&#xA;regular polygon is the angle formed by two consecutive rays of the&#xA;circle passing through the vertices of the polygon. Since the polygon&#xA;is regular, all these angles at the center are equal.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
